@@ -0,0 +1,88 @@
+# Delta for Retrieval (GraphRAG)
+
+## ADDED Requirements
+
+### Requirement: Hybrid retrieval pipeline
+The retrieval pipeline SHALL execute the ordered stages
+**Resolve → Vector-Recall → Lexical-Recall → Fuse → Rerank →
+Graph-Traverse → Ground**. The graph traversal MUST be the
+authoritative source of facts presented to the LLM; vector and lexical
+recall serve only as candidate generators for `Clause` nodes.
+
+#### Scenario: Pipeline ordering
+- GIVEN a user question about coverage for a specific disease
+- WHEN the retriever processes the query
+- THEN entities (Party, Product, Peril) are resolved first
+- AND candidate clauses are recalled by vector + lexical search
+- AND the candidates are reranked before graph traversal
+- AND only after the Cypher traversal is the LLM invoked.
+
+### Requirement: Vector + lexical fusion
+Top-k candidate clauses SHALL be drawn from the `clause_text_embeddings`
+vector index (k=20) **and** the full-text index over
+`Clause.title`/`Clause.text_content`. The two lists MUST be fused using
+Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF) before reranking.
+
+#### Scenario: Lexical fallback catches rare named perils
+- GIVEN a query mentioning a rare named peril absent from the embedding
+        model's training distribution
+- WHEN the vector recall returns it at rank > 20
+- THEN the lexical recall MUST return it within its top-20
+- AND RRF fusion places it in the reranker input.
+
+### Requirement: Reranking
+A cross-encoder reranker SHALL reduce the fused candidate list to at
+most 5 clauses before the graph traversal. The retriever MUST log the
+reranker score alongside each surviving clause.
+
+#### Scenario: Top-5 cap respected
+- GIVEN 20 fused candidate clauses
+- WHEN the reranker scores them
+- THEN at most 5 clauses are forwarded to the Cypher executor.
+
+### Requirement: As-of graph traversal
+The graph traversal SHALL accept an optional `as_of: Date` parameter and
+filter edges by `valid_from ≤ as_of ≤ coalesce(valid_to, as_of)`. The
+default `as_of` is "now".
+
+#### Scenario: Historical coverage answered correctly
+- GIVEN an endorsement effective 2025-06-01 removed a coverage
+- WHEN the user asks about coverage as of 2025-03-15
+- THEN the traversal MUST return the pre-endorsement coverage
+- AND the answer cites the original clause.
+
+### Requirement: Authoritative Cypher template
+The traversal SHALL use the parameterised template under
+`assets/cypher/10_graphrag_lookup.cypher`. Free-form Cypher generated by
+the LLM is forbidden for production queries. New traversal templates
+MUST be added via a future OpenSpec change.
+
+#### Scenario: LLM-generated Cypher rejected
+- GIVEN the LLM produces a Cypher string at runtime
+- WHEN the executor receives it
+- THEN it MUST refuse to execute and log a security event.
+
+### Requirement: Citation contract
+Every answer surfaced to the user MUST cite at least one Clause by its
+`id` and `title`. The serving layer MUST verify that each cited
+`clause_id` is present in the sub-graph returned by the Cypher
+traversal; otherwise the answer is rejected and regenerated.
+
+#### Scenario: Hallucinated citation rejected
+- GIVEN the LLM answer references `CL_999` which is not in the
+        retrieved sub-graph
+- WHEN the validator inspects the citation set
+- THEN the answer is rejected
+- AND a regeneration is requested with a stricter prompt.
+
+### Requirement: Exclusion takes precedence over coverage
+If the same `RiskPeril` is reachable via both `[:COVERS]` and
+`[:EXCLUDES]` edges from clauses of the same active policy, the
+answerer MUST report **not covered** and surface the exclusion clause.
+
+#### Scenario: Conflicting clauses
+- GIVEN peril P is covered by clause CA and excluded by clause CB on the
+        same active policy
+- WHEN the user asks whether P is covered
+- THEN the answer states the peril is excluded
+- AND cites CB.
